{
  "texts": [
    "These findings indicate that we can implement this model in a clinical setting to speed up and accurately identify colorectal polyps, a crucial process for cancer diagnosis and treatment.",
    "The results obtained from the PolynetDWTCADx framework are very robust; far better, with respect to colorectal cancer detection and segmentation, compared to the baseline models.",
    "On the classification tasks, it achieved, on all classes, a test accuracy of 92.3%, precision of 91.8%, recall of 92.7%, and an F1-score of 92.2%.",
    "Similarly, the segmentation performed using U-Net resulted in IoU of 0.93 and DC of 0.96, hence showing the effectiveness of this technique in cancerous tissue delineation.",
    "The detailed comparison carried out with standalone CNNs and U-Net models further shows its superior performance."
  ]
}